reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2020
reviews.name: B1llb3rt
reviews.title: Love this Board!
reviews.review: Chose this board for my Ryzen 5000 build over the Asus Tuf Gaming x570 plus wifi because of the qflash BIOS feature. BIOS flash worked perfectly and recognized my 5600x without issue. the only drawback I see so far is the system fan header positioning. I required a splitter and an extension to get my three front case fans working due to the positioning of the fan headers near the IO shield. I'm still giving it 5 stars despite this issue.

reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2020
reviews.name: Amazon Customer
reviews.title: Great board, but needs BIOS update for Ryzen 5000
reviews.review: Didn't realize this board didn't come ready for Ryzen 5000. The amazing Q-flash+ feature saved the day though. Normally you need a supported CPU installed just to do a BIOS update (meaning I would've had to find a Ryzen 3000 CPU), but Q-flash+ lets you update straight off of a USB stick with no CPU installed. What a lifesaver

reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2020
reviews.name: Andrew Koors
reviews.title: TRASH BOARD FOR Q FLASHING FOR RYZEN 5000 PROCESSORS
reviews.review: DO NOT BUY THIS BOARD FOR RYZEN 5000 PROCESSORS. THE Q FLASH IS THE ABSOLUTE WORST OUT OF ANY BOARD. NO INDICATORS. TRIED 4 DIFFERENT FLASH DRIVES WATCHED EVERY VIDEO AND GUIDE KNOWN TO MAN AND STILL WONT Q FLASH. SPEND THE LITTLE EXTRA MONEY ON A BOARD THAT HAS THE FULL Q FLASH BUTTON ON THE BACK WITH INDICATORS. WASTED 3 DAYS OF MY TIME WITH THIS BOARD.

reviews.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2020
reviews.name: loucarisma
reviews.title: nightmare bios
reviews.review: I,ve been building computers for over 30 years. Ibought this mb to replace a fully functional msi x470 mb for the new ryzen processors coming out. This motherboard wont run my memory at 3200 with the timings set in the bios constant bsod,s and unstable. Thought it doesnt like my ram(functional btw on my old board) its hynix chips so I pulled the ram from my grandsons computer (samsung bdie chips) both corsair vengeance ram still bsods and unstable. so i thought i,d run it at 2933 WRONG then no video signal had to reset bios and leave the defaults atn 2133 mhz. This is absolutely unacceptable with proven ram sticks one hynix and one from samsung i,m about to return this garbage and stick with my msi x470 gaming pro carbon. i would not recommend this to anyone two days of fine tuning the bios settings to no avail. if i could give this zero stars i would.
